********************************************************************************
************************ NEXT COMMIT DESCRIPTION *******************************
********************************************************************************

The print() function for printing the stacks for debugging was improved
to print the elements sorting metadata.

A member left_to_pre_sort member was added to main t_ps_stacks struct.

A new functions collection for a more complex list node data type was
written. This collection replaces the obsolete ps_dlclst_int_utils. In
addition to re-writing the previous functions, the following were added
to get element members and to obtain an integer array from the element
list:
get_cost_a()
get_cost_b()
get_pos_when_sorted()
get_value()
list_to_array()

In the sort collection, the following functions were added:
classic_sorting(): to sort the integer array
set_pos_when_sorted(): to use the sorted integer array to initialize
the pos_when_sorted members of the elements in the list.



